{"word":"ἀμελής","slug":"ἀμελής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμελής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>α</el> privat. , <el>μέλει</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>careless, heedless, negligent</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἀμελῶς</el>, <i>carelessly</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>ἀμελέστερον</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>careless of</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>περί τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀμελῶς ἔχειν</el> <i>to be careless</i>, <el>πρός τι πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>uncared for, unheeded</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}